Date: Thu, 27 May 2004 10:48:46 -0400
From: Joseph Dudley <jdudley@intellibridge.com>
Source: News 24 (South Africa) [edited]
<http://www.news24.com/News24/Africa/News/0,,2-11-1447_1532997,00.html>

Toxic grain kills 26 Kenyans
------------------------
At least 48 people have died in Kenya's Eastern Province in the past 3
weeks after consuming maize that became poisonous because of humid storage
conditions, a medical official said on Wednesday.
"At least 34 people have died of the same symptoms in Makueni district and
14 others in Kitui district by this morning (Wednesday)," the ministry
official who asked not to be named, said by telephone.
The official said that a total of 102 cases of aflatoxin poisoning - the
result of fungal growth on maize - had been reported in the eastern Makueni
and Kitui districts since May 6, although the problem started around March
this year.
[By: Anthea Jonathan]
