[While the 2 newswires have slightly differing figures, there have been an
increase in at least 10 additional deaths, and it appears as though at
least 100 individuals have had significant health consequences as a result
of this aflatoxin contamination. In the 2001 report of a similar
occurrence (see ProMED-mail Aflatoxicosis, human - Kenya 20011007.2427)
there were reports of 24 cases with 12 deaths in North Meru. - Mod.MPP]
